OL,6,FSenior Crown prosecutor Ed Hall, said:
OL,7,F"Rather than face justice, Hallows
OL,8,Ffled to Dubai with the help of his
OL,9,Fgirlfriend, Paris Askew. Knowing he
OL,10,Fwas responsible for murder, she
OL,11,Farranged his transport and provided
OL,12,Ffinancial support while he evaded
OL,13,Fcapture.
OL,15,F"Our prosecutors presented clear
OL,16,Fevidence of her role in obstructing
OL,17,Fthe course of justice.
